5
6 PART I. TROPICAL STORM CHANTAL FUNDING AND OTHER DISASTER
7 RECOVERY
8
9 SUBPART I-A. LEGISLATIVE FINDINGS AND SCOPE
10 SECTION 1A.1.(a) Legislative Findings. – The General Assembly finds that on July
11 6, 2025, Tropical Storm Chantal impacted the central region of North Carolina, resulting in
12 several days of severe weather, including flooding, high winds, and tornadoes, necessitating
13 recovery efforts in the impacted area of this State. On July 25, 2025, the United States Small
14 Business Administration issued a disaster declaration for several counties in the State. On August
15 5, 2025, the Governor declared a Type I disaster in the impacted area due to the effects of Tropical
16 Storm Chantal. On September 11, 2025, the President of the United States issued a major disaster
17 declaration in accordance with the Stafford Act (P.L. 93-288) for multiple counties in the State,
18 approving public assistance federal funding for affected counties.
19 SECTION 1A.1.(b) Applicability. – Except as otherwise provided, funds
20 appropriated in this Part apply only to the counties listed in this section.
21 SECTION 1A.1.(c) Scope. – Funds appropriated and allocated in this Part for
22 Tropical Storm Chantal shall only be expended to support disaster relief and recovery efforts in
23 the impacted area. For the purposes of this Part, the term "impacted area" means Alamance,
24 Caswell, Chatham, Durham, Granville, Moore, Orange, Person, and Wake Counties.
25
26 SUBPART I-B. TROPICAL STORM CHANTAL AND OTHER DISASTER RECOVERY
27 APPROPRIATIONS
28 SECTION 1B.1.(a) There is appropriated from the State Emergency Response and
29 Disaster Relief Fund the sum of sixty-five million five hundred thousand dollars ($65,500,000)
30 in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year as follows:
31 (1) Fifty-five million dollars ($55,000,000) to the Department of Public Safety,
32 Division of Emergency Management (NCEM), for the State Match Fund
33 (Budget Code 24552, Budget Fund 206628), established in Section 5.9(d) of
34 S.L. 2021-180, in the following amounts:
