6 SECTION 2.11.(o) G.S. 130A-309.28 reads as rewritten:
7 "§ 130A-309.28. University research.
8 Research, training, and service activities related to solid and hazardous waste management
9 conducted by The University of North Carolina shall be coordinated by the Board of Governors
10 of The University of North Carolina through the Office of the President. Proposals for research
11 contracts and grants; public service assignments; and responses to requests for information and
12 technical assistance by the State and units of local government, business, and industry shall be
13 addressed by a formal process involving an advisory board of university personnel appointed by
14 the President and chaired and directed by an individual appointed by the President. The Board of
15 Governors of The University of North Carolina shall consult with the Department in developing
16 the research programs and provide the Department with a copy of the proposed research program
17 for review and comment before the research is undertaken. Research contracts shall be awarded
18 to independent nonprofit colleges and universities within the State which are accredited by a
19 regional preferred accrediting agency, as defined in G.S. 116-11.4, on the same basis as those
20 research contracts awarded to The University of North Carolina. Research activities shall include
21 the following areas:
22 (1) Methods and processes for recycling solid and hazardous waste.
23 (2) Methods of treatment for detoxifying hazardous waste.
24 (3) Technologies for disposing of solid and hazardous waste."
