11 Funds appropriated by this section do not revert but remain available for these
12 purposes. Payments authorized under this subsection may be made to a county, a rural
13 development authority, or as reimbursements to an eligible business, as specified in the
14 agreement or agreements required under subsection (b) of this section. Appropriations for public
15 roads authorized under this subsection may be transferred to the Department of Transportation,
16 as deemed necessary or beneficial by the Department. For purposes of this section, an "eligible
17 business" is a manufacturer of steel forgings and large diameter steel fabrications, and a "project
18 site" is an industrial manufacturing site in Hertford County with direct access to the Chowan
19 River.
20 SECTION 4.4.(b) Agreement. – Prior to the allocation of any funds appropriated by
21 this section, the Department shall enter into an agreement or agreements with Hertford County
22 (County), the Hertford County Rural Development Authority (Authority), or both, and an eligible
23 business. Agreements entered into under this subsection are binding and constitute a continuing
24 contractual obligation of each party to the agreements. The agreement or agreements shall
25 include, at a minimum, the following provisions:
26 (1) A provision requiring the eligible business to (i) invest at least nine hundred
27 seventy-four million dollars ($974,000,000) of private funds in the project site
28 and (ii) create and maintain at least 835 new jobs having an overall average
29 compensation that exceeds one hundred seventy-five percent (175%) of the
30 average wage for all insured private employers in the county in which the
31 project site is located. For purposes of this subdivision, "new job" shall have
32 the same meaning as "eligible position" under G.S. 143B-437.51,
33 notwithstanding the base period applicable to that section. The Department
34 shall determine the relevant periods during which the eligible business must
35 meet the requirements of this subdivision.
36 (2) One or more provisions addressing all the performance criteria, remedies, and
37 other safeguards required by the Department to secure the State's benefit
38 derived from (i) the permitting, engineering, design, and construction of a
39 publicly owned dock at the project site and (ii) the construction of a public
40 road at the project site, including a provision ensuring that the benefits to the
41 State from such activity outweigh the costs.
42 (3) A provision requiring the eligible business to repay an appropriate,
43 proportionate amount for any failure by the business to meet and maintain the
44 applicable performance criteria on which State funds appropriated by this
45 section were based.
46 (4) A provision prohibiting the eligible business from seeking or accepting any
47 grant pursuant to Part 2G or Part 2H of Article 10 of Chapter 143B of the
48 General Statutes for any jobs created because of appropriations made under
49 this section.
50 (5) A provision requiring that State funds appropriated by this section be allocated
51 only for expenses incurred for (i) permitting, engineering, and design of, or
